Competition: Pan American Games
Season: 1983
BlockSource: http://www.rsssf.com/tablesp/panam83.html

* 1983 JUEGOS PANAMERICANOS (Pan-American Games)
* For amateur players.
* QUALIFYING

Round: Qualifying Round

* North America:

7/6/1983; United States; 1-1; Canada; Giants Stadium
ave Lischner 8; Igor Vrablic 15
United States: Jeff Duback, Dan D'Angelo, Mike Fox, Tom Isirov (Amr Aly), Jim Kavanaugh, Dave Lischner, Doug Puffenbarger (Jeff Hooker), Tim Schulz, Bobby Smith, John Stollmeyer, Kazbek Tambi
Canada: Don Ferguson, John Connor, Paul Lee, Jamie Lowery, Craig Martin, Ed McNally, Norm Odinga, George Pakos (Robbie Cleugh), Alan Spink, Dan Sudeyko, Igor Vrablic

7/10/1983; Canada; 2-3; United States; McMaster Stadium, Hamilton, ON; Rex Osborne
Dan Sudeyko, Norm Odinga 87; Mike Fox 12, Mike Fox 51, Jeff Hooker 62
Canada: Don Ferguson, John Connor (Robbie Cleugh), Ken Garraway (Norm Odinga), Paul Lee, Jamie Lowery, Craig Martin, Ed McNally, George Pakos, Alan Spink, Dan Sudeyko, Igor Vrablic
United States: Tim Harris, Amr Aly, Paul Caligiuri, Dale Ervine (Dan D'Angelo), Mike Fox, Jeff Hooker, Jim Kavanaugh, Dave Lischner, Kevin Maher, John Stollmeyer, Kazbek Tambi.

* USA qualified 4-3 on aggregate.

* Central America and Caribbean:
* Presumably Mexico, Cuba, and Bermuda qualified based on their positions in the 1982 Juegos
* Centroamericanos y del Caribe. It is not clear how Guatemala qualified.


* South America:

* Venezuela qualified as hosts.
* Brazil, Uruguay, and Argentina qualified as the top three teams in the 
* 1983 South American Youth Championship.  Bolivia (who were fourth) withdrew and were replaced by Chile.

* FINAL TOURNAMENT - Caracas, Venezuela
* The original draw was:
* Group A: Chile, Surinam, Venezuela
* Group B: Bermuda, Brazil, USA
* Group C: Argentina, Guatemala, Honduras
* Group D: Cuba, Mexico, Uruguay
* However Surinam and Honduras did not arrive, and the draw was changed at the last minute.

